    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "\n*Followup to https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/30889*\n\n### Problem\n\n\n`vim.ui.img` emits termcodes directly, instead of UI events. That means it doesn't work on GUIs such as Neovide.\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFormalize UI events for image display.\n\nThis may require designing a way to *stream* data instead of placing a giant image in 1 event? That might be unusual, so maybe we can ignore that for now...",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@justinmk I was playing around with this. It's the first time I've tried to delve into the C code other than that one small thing I tried with `imgprog` from the big PR.\n\nDo you have more thoughts here? So far, I was thinking of three events tied to an ext_images that would need to be opted into.\n\n1. img_show(id, data, opts)\n2. img_update(id, opts)\n3. img_delete(id)",
